    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Confessions of a Closet Homemaker</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Natalie Mizrachi letter calls Carolynn Carreno's April 30 Lives column disturbing and tragic for trying to make excuses for wanting to make people happy</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Carreno's article struck me as tragic. Here is a woman who admirably is trying to fulfill herself in a most unselfish way. Yet she feels compelled to tell us that she has a real life other than that of making others happy. That creating a warm domestic environment can become something to be ashamed of is disturbing.</p>
        <p>Natalie Mizrachi  Brooklyn</p>
      </block>
